<paragraph blockId="35.[144,759,1483,1903]" pageId="35" pageNumber="409">
dark-green dorsum, without markings (
<typeStatus box="[654,754,1483,1505]" pageId="35" pageNumber="409">holotype</typeStatus>
, BNHS 4433, 
<figureCitation box="[300,397,1514,1536]" captionStart="Figure 27" captionStartId="35.[144,223,1356,1375]" captionTargetBox="[148,757,196,1326]" captionTargetId="figure-496@35.[148,757,196,1326]" captionTargetPageId="35" captionText="Figure 27. Philautus chromasynchysi sp. nov. A, holotype (BNHS 4433); B, paratype (BNHS 4438); C, paratype (BNHS 4442): all from Kurichiyarmala." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5445410" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5445410/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="409">Fig. 27A</figureCitation>
) in life, turns uniform greyish black in preservation; (2) dorsal skin prominently horny spinular, uniform greyish brown dorsum with dark discontinuous concave lines on either side, from just behind the eye level to vent (BNHS 4438, 
<figureCitation box="[144,242,1667,1689]" captionStart="Figure 27" captionStartId="35.[144,223,1356,1375]" captionTargetBox="[148,757,196,1326]" captionTargetId="figure-496@35.[148,757,196,1326]" captionTargetPageId="35" captionText="Figure 27. Philautus chromasynchysi sp. nov. A, holotype (BNHS 4433); B, paratype (BNHS 4438); C, paratype (BNHS 4442): all from Kurichiyarmala." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5445410" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5445410/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="409">Fig. 27B</figureCitation>
); (3) uniform yellowish green dorsum with dark minute spots, groin dark brown with golden yellow blotches, lateral region golden yellow (
<typeStatus box="[152,256,1759,1780]" pageId="35" pageNumber="409">paratype</typeStatus>
, BNHS 4442, 
<figureCitation box="[426,525,1758,1781]" captionStart="Figure 27" captionStartId="35.[144,223,1356,1375]" captionTargetBox="[148,757,196,1326]" captionTargetId="figure-496@35.[148,757,196,1326]" captionTargetPageId="35" captionText="Figure 27. Philautus chromasynchysi sp. nov. A, holotype (BNHS 4433); B, paratype (BNHS 4438); C, paratype (BNHS 4442): all from Kurichiyarmala." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5445410" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5445410/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="409">Fig. 27C</figureCitation>
); (4) sparsely horny spinular skin, dorsum light green with a pair of faint concave lines, an inverted dark triangular patch in between the eyes (directed downwards), lateral region light-yellowish grey, anterior surface of thighs light
</paragraph>
